original: Zetterlöf, Tage, advokat, Göteborg, f. 5/3/05 i Partille, Gbgs o. Boh. L, av dir. Gustaf Z. o. Victoria Malmsten. G. 35 m. Karin Peterson. Barn: Margaretha f. 38, Barbro 39, Eva 45. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 24, styrmans-o. sjökapt:ex. i Gbg 29, jur. kand. i Sthlm 34. Anst. i adv: firman WilHam A. Crump & Son i London 34, å dispa-schörskönt, i Gbg 34-35, i adv:firman Haight, Griffin, Deming & Gardner i New York 35-36, i adv:firman Wikström & Sjögren i Gbg 35, sed. 43 del-äg. i adv:byrån Adv. Mannheimer o.
translated: Zetterlöf, Tage, lawyer, Gothenburg, b. 5/3/05 in Partille, Gothenburg and Bohus County. Son of director Gustaf Z. and Victoria Malmsten. Married in 1935 to Karin Peterson. Children: Margaretha b. 1938, Barbro b. 1939, Eva b. 1945. Education: Graduate from Gothenburg Higher Latin School in 1924, helmsman and ship captain exam in Gothenburg in 1929, law degree in Stockholm in 1934. Employment: Worked at the law firm WilHam A. Crump & Son in London in 1934, dispatched clerk in Gothenburg in 1934-1935, worked at the law firm Haight, Griffin, Deming & Gardner in New York in 1935-1936, worked at the law firm Wikström & Sjögren in Gothenburg in 1935, and became a partial owner of the law office Adv. Mannheimer in 1943.
